<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,692,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[910,978,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">rectus</emphasis>
(straight), referring to the uncus with posterior margin nearly straight in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
